Description: Fragment of handle of East Greek pottery krater; 'metallic', twisted, ring handle pendent from ribbed 'spool'; broken off at top and back. Streakily glazed save for underside of spool at junction with lost wall.
Curator's comments: Probably from the same vessel as 1965,0930.471. A more elaborate version than on British Museum 1886,0401,1312 and 1313.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1111)
